Comments: pop and GDPpcp for the 2021 and 2014 from Wikipedia; GDPpcp2014 reported as GDPpcp2010. GDP nominal for 2020 estimated at US$307 million. pop for 2010 estimated by linear interpolation on a log scale from numbers given at 15,506. That gives GDPpcn2020 of $19,799. Wikipedia accessed 2024-11-14.

Wikipedia "Antarctica" says, "Population 1,300 to 5,100 (seasonal)". No year was given for those numbers, and no GDP numbers. We may not need GDP without some deaths and more events. Wikip. accessed 2024-11-07.

Wikipedia "Guernsey" says the population was estimated at 67,334 for 2016 and GDPpcp in 2003 was £33,123. A British pound bought roughly 1.60 USD that year. We will use that exchange rate and ignore the difference between 2003 and 2020. The article also gave a nominal GDP of USD 4,513.63 million without giving a year or a source. We divide that by the 2016 population and use that as GDPpcn2020. Accessed 2024-11-14.

Wikipedia "Jersey" says, 2021 census of 103,267, a GDPpcp in 2015 of about £45,783 and a GDPpcn for 2019 of roughly  £45,320. One GBP bought on average 1.5285 USD in 2015 but only 1.2772 in 2019. Accessed 2024-11-14.
The World Bank had population but not GDP data for the British Virgin Islands. Wikipedia said they had GDPpcp in 2017 of roughly $34,200. Accessed 2024-11-14.
Wikipedia "Caribbean Netherlands" says, 2024 population estimate 30.000 and 2023 GDP UD$725 million. Accessed 2024-11-15.
Wikipedia "Christmas Island" says, 2021 population estimate 1,692 with a nominal 2010 GDP estimated at $52.1 million, which appears to be USD, not Australian dollar.

Wikipedia "Cook Islands" says they are self-governing in free association with  New Zealand with a 2021 population of 15,040 and a nominal GDP estimated at $384 million USD for 2020. Accessed 2024-11-15.
World Bank reported population but no GDP data for Eritrea for 2020:2023. Wikipedia gave GDP nominal and PPP = 566 and 1,835, respectively, for 2019. We use those both for 2020. Accessed 2024-11-15.
Wikipedia "Falkland Islands" says they are a British overseas territory with a 2021 population of 15,040 and a GDPpcp estimated at $96,962 for 2013. We ignore the difference between 2013 and 2020.

Wikipedia "French Guiana" says it is "is an overseas department and region of France located on the northern coast of South America". Its 2024 population is 295,385. It has a 2022 GDP of 4.56199 billion Euros. Over 2022, one Euro averaged 1.0535 USD. Accessed 2024-11-15

Gibraltar was in the World Bank data we extracted but without GDP data. Wikipedia said its GDPpcp for 2013 was £50,941 and GDPpcn for 2024 of £85,614. We found exchange rates for 2013 and 2023 of 1 GBP = 1.5647 and 1.2440 USD, respectively. Accessed 2024-11-15

Wikipedia "Guadeloupe" says it "is an overseas department and region of France in the Caribbean." Its population 2024-01-01 was 378,561. The source it cited for regional GDP gave 10.489 billion Euros for 2022. That year one Euro bought on average 1.0535 USD. Accessed 2024-11-15.

Wikipedia "Kosovo" says it "is a landlocked country in Southeast" Europe with partial diplomatic recognition." Our World Bank data does not have separate numbers for it. 2024 pop = 1,586,659, GDPpcp = $16,775, and GDPpcn = $6389. We ignore the difference between 2023 and 2024. Accessed 2024-11-15.
Our World Bank extract on Liechtenstein included population but not GDP data. Wikipedia gave GDPpcp = $98,432 and GDPpcn = $187,267 for 2014 and 2020, respectively. Accessed 2024-11-15.

Wikipedia "Martinique" says it is an overseas department of France with a population of 349,925 in 2024-01-01 and a GDPpc of 24,700 Euros. We assume that is GDPpcn2023, during which 1 Euro bought on average 1.0821 USD. Accessed 2024-11-15.

Wikipedia "Mayotte" says it is an overseas department of France with a population of 320,901 in 2024-01. Eurostat, cited by Wikipedia, gave its 2022 GDP at 3.34679 billion Euros. The exchange rate in 2022 averaged 1.0535 USD per Euro. Accessed 2024-11-15.

Wikipedia "Montserrat" says it is a British overseas territory with a 2022 population of 4,390 and a nominal GDP for 2019 of US$181,680,000. We ignore the difference between 2019, 2020, and 2022. Accessed 2024-11-15.

Wikipedia "New Caledonia" says it is a sui generis collectivity of France in the Southwest Pacific. Our World Bank extract provided population but not GDP data. Wikipedia gave GDPpcn for 2019 of US$34,780. We report the latter for 2020. Accessed 2024-11-15.

Wikipedia "Niue" says it is a self-governing island country in free association with New Zealand, a 2021 population of 1,937, a GDPpcp for 2019 of $5,800 and a nominal GDP for 2021 of 38 million USD. Accessed 2024-11-15.
We got population but not GDP data for North Korea from the World Bank. Wikipedia estimated its GDPpcp for 2015 at $1,800 and its GDPpcn for 2019 at $640. Accessed 2024-11-15.

Wikipedia "Reunion" says it is a French overseas department with a 2024-01 population of 885,700 and a 2022 GDPpcn of €24,465. The exchange rate for that year averaged 1.0535 USD per Euro. Accessed 2024-11-15.

Wikipedia "Saint Pierre and Miquelon" says it is a French archipelago of eight islands near Newfoundland with a 2020 population of 6,092 and GDPpcp for 2004 estimated at €26,073. In 2004, one Euro bought between 1.19 and 1.35 USD. We will use the $1.35 per Euro and ignore the difference between nominal and PPP and between 2004 and 2020 for current purposes. If Saint Pierre and Miquelon is chosen for further study, these numbers can be replaced by better data. Accessed 2024-11-15.

Wikipedia "Saint Barthélemy" says it is an overseas collectivity of France with a 2022 population estimated at 10,967 and a GDPpcn 2014 estimated at $51,735. For present purposes, we ignore the difference between 2014 and 2020. Accessed 2024-11-15.

Our World Bank data extract gave population but not GDP data for "St. Martin (French part)". The Wikipedia article on "Economy of Saint Martin (island)" estimates GDPpcn for 2008 at $15,400. Accessed 2024-11-15.
Our World Bank data extract gave population but not GDP data for South Sudan. The Wikipedia article on it estimated GDPpcp2022 = $934 and GDPpcn2022 = $326. Accessed 2024-11-15.
Wikipedia "Taiwan" says its population was estimated 2022-07-01 at 23,894,394 and had GDPpcp and GDPpcn estimated at $72,485 and $32,339, respectively, for 2023. Accessed 2024-11-15.

Wikipedia "Tolelau" says its population was estimated for 2016 at 1,499 and had a nominal GDPpc in 2017 estimated at $6,275 We record both those numbers for 2020, ignoring the difference in dates. Accessed 2024-11-15.

Wikipedia "Vatican City" says its population was estimated for 2023 at 764 and its GDPpcp for 2021 was estimated at €19,450.22. During 2021, one Euro could buy on average 1.1828 USD. Accessed 2024-11-14.
World Bank gave population but not GDP for Venezuela. Wikipedia gave GDPpcp = $7,985 and GDPpcn = $3,474 for 2023. Accessed 2024-11-14.
Wikipedia "Wallis and Fortuna" says its population was estimated for 2023 at 11,151 and its GDPpcn for 2005 was estimated at $12,640.
World Bank provided population data on Yemen but no GDP info. Wikipedia says its GDPpcp2023 = $2,053 and GDPpcn2023 = $617. Accessed 2024-11-15.
